###
# Ares Backend API - Test Requests
# Usa questo file con REST Client extension per VS Code o Thunder Client
###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### Welcome / Info
GET {{baseUrl}}

### Health Check
GET {{apiUrl}}/health

### ============================================
### AUTH ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Registra nuovo utente
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "username": "testplayer"
}

### Registra secondo utente
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "player2@example.com",
  "password": "securepass456",
  "username": "player2"
}

### Test validazione - Email mancante (dovrebbe fallire)
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "password123",
  "username": "testplayer"
}

### Test validazione - Password troppo corta (dovrebbe fallire)
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "123",
  "username": "testplayer"
}

### Test validazione - Username troppo corto (dovrebbe fallire)
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "username": "ab"
}

### Ottieni utente per UID (sostituisci YOUR_USER_UID con un UID reale)
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/user/YOUR_USER_UID

### Ottieni utente per username
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/user/username/testplayer

### Ottieni utente per username (utente non esistente)
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/user/username/nonexistent

### Elimina utente (sostituisci YOUR_USER_UID con un UID reale)
DELETE {{apiUrl}}/auth/user/YOUR_USER_UID

### ============================================
### LEGACY ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Legacy - Get Name
GET {{baseUrl}}/name

### Legacy - Get Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/status

### Test 404 - Endpoint non esistente
GET {{baseUrl}}/nonexistent-endpoint

